    "description": "<p>This spell causes confusion among creatures within a 30' radius (60' across). The spell affects 3-18 creatures in the area, with victims under 2 + 1 Hit Dice automatically failing their saves. Creatures with 2 + 1 or more Hit Dice can attempt a saving throw vs. spells each round they remain in the area to avoid confusion.</p><p><strong>Effects of Confusion:</strong> Each round, the DM rolls [[/r 2d6 #confusion effect]] for each affected creature to determine its action, according to the table below:</p><p><strong>Confusion Results</strong></p><table style=\"width:95%\"><thead><tr><th>2d6 Roll</th><th>Result</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>2-5</td><td>Attack the spellcaster's party</td></tr><tr><td>6-8</td><td>Do nothing</td></tr><tr><td>9-12</td><td>Attack the creature's own party</td></tr></tbody></table>",
